<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1811,2034]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,605,1878,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479">A brief description of the specimen.</emphasis>
An 
<taxonomicName box="[653,783,1877,1901]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Epinephelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[653,783,1877,1901]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="479">Epinephelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with emarginate caudal fin, 
<number box="[1175,1201,1878,1901]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="84.0">84</number>
series of scales along the body; dorsal fin with 
<number box="[423,448,1911,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="11.0">11</number>
spines and 
<number box="[576,603,1911,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="14.0">14</number>
rays; anal fin with 
<number box="[814,827,1911,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="3.0">3</number>
spines and 
<number box="[955,968,1911,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="8.0">8</number>
rays; pectoral fins with 
<number box="[1230,1256,1911,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="17.0">17</number>
rays; pelvic fins with a spine and 
<number box="[329,342,1945,1968]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="5.0">5</number>
rays. Gill rakers on lower limb of first gill arch 12, 1 at angle of the arch and 
<docIssue box="[1157,1170,1945,1968]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479">
<number box="[1157,1170,1945,1968]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="4.0">4</number>
</docIssue>
rakers on upper limb + 
<number box="[1422,1435,1945,1968]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="4.0">4</number>
rudimentary gill rakers. Rear margin of preopercle serrate, with small spines at its lower angle (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1213,1978,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,921,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,921,1890]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 2. Epinephelus areolatus (Forsskål, 1775) from the Mediterranean. The arrow indicates the small spines on the lower angle preopercle. SMNHTAU—P 15834. Photo O. Rittner." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270634/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="479">
Fig. 
<number box="[1197,1213,1978,2001]" pageId="0" pageNumber="479" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). First dorsal spine is above the origin of upper pectoral ray. Pelvic fin begins below a vertical line from the origin of lowest pectoral ray.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
